President Donald J. Trump has issued a proclamation declaring September 6-8, 2019, as National Days of Prayer and Remembrance to honor the memory of the victims of the September 11, 2001 terrorist attacks. The proclamation emphasizes the magnitude of the loss and the courage, compassion, strength, and unity displayed during that tragic event. It calls for prayer, contemplation, memorial services, visiting memorials, ringing bells, and evening candlelight remembrance vigils as ways to mark these days. The proclamation also invites people around the world to join in these Days of Prayer and Remembrance.